title: Internal Compiler Error working with Enum, Match

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
### Code ``` enum Location { Unknown, Anonymous, Known(f64,f64) } impl Location { fn display(&self) { match *self { Location::Unknown => println!("Location unknown"), Location::Anonymous => println!("Location anonymous"), Location::Known(lat,lon) => println!("Latitude: {}, Longitude: {}", lat, lon) } } } fn main() { let address = Location::Unknown; address.display(); let address = Location::Anonymous; address.display(); let address = Location::Known(28.608295, -80.604177); address.display(); } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.60.0 (7737e0b5c 2022-04-04) binary: rustc commit-hash: 7737e0b5c4103216d6fd8cf941b7ab9bdbaace7c commit-date: 2022-04-04 host: aarch64-apple-darwin release: 1.60.0 LLVM version: 14.0.0 ``` ### Error output ``` could not compile `challenge14` Caused by: process didn't exit successfully: `/Users/michaeldavila/.cargo/bin/rustc --crate-name challenge14 --edition=2021 src/main.rs --error-format=json --json=diagnostic-rendered-ansi,artifacts,future-incompat --crate-type bin --emit=dep-info,link -C embed-bitcode=no -C split-debuginfo=unpacked -C debuginfo=2 -C metadata=3a20c5034e3db8b2 -C extra-filename=-3a20c5034e3db8b2 --out-dir /Users/michaeldavila/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-UniversityofTexasatArlington/CLionProjects/challenge14/target/debug/deps -C incremental=/Users/michaeldavila/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-UniversityofTexasatArlington/CLionProjects/challenge14/target/debug/incremental -L dependency=/Users/michaeldavila/Library/CloudStorage/OneDrive-UniversityofTexasatArlington/CLionProjects/challenge14/target/debug/deps` (signal: 6, SIGABRT: process abort signal) Process finished with exit code 101 ```
